Article 95ter of the Luxembourgish Constitution. 

                     

                  
 

                     
   
The proposal for a constitutional revision dates back to 15 May 2009, but the provision relating to the Ombudsman institution was added later. It was part of the version sent to the Venice Commission for an opinion on 6 June 2018. 

                     

                  
 

                     
   
Council of Europe: Venice Commission opinion (CDL-AD(2019)005): ‘
The Ombudsman institution, including its mandate, shall be based on a firm legal foundation, preferably at constitutional level, while its characteristics and functions may be further elaborated at the statutory level.
’
